<ArticleLayout
  title="Australian Status Labels"
  description="How Australian Home Collective describes Australian ownership, local shipping, local support and product-status claims."
  category="Product Details"
  date="Updated July 2026"
  readingTime="3 minute read"
  showDisclosure={false}
>
  <p>
    This page explains how we describe Australian ownership, local shipping, local support and
    other product-status claims. The goal is to make product details easier to compare without
    overstating what a label means.
  </p>

  <h2>What the labels mean</h2>
  <ul class="feature-list">
    <li><strong>Australian brand:</strong> used when a brand appears to be based in Australia.</li>
    <li><strong>Australian made:</strong> used only where the claim is clear and should still be checked with the brand.</li>
    <li><strong>Local shipping:</strong> used where Australian delivery or local dispatch appears relevant to readers.</li>
    <li><strong>Local support:</strong> used where Australian customer support, warranty handling or service information is part of the comparison.</li>
    <li><strong>Useful alternative:</strong> used where something may still be worth considering even if it is not presented as Australian owned or made.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to check</h2>
  <p>
    Product details can change. Before relying on an origin, shipping or support claim, check
    the current information from the brand, product label or relevant support page.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
